5.2. Pre-training for other datasets

We also examine how our dataset can help with a real- world document digitization application. When digitizing new publications, researchers usually do not generate large scale ground truth data to train their layout analysis models. If they are able to adapt our dataset, or models trained on our dataset, to develop models on their data, they can build their pipelines more efficiently and develop more accurate models. To this end, we conduct two experiments. First we examine how layout analysis models trained on the main pages can be used for understanding index pages. More- cover, we study how the pre-trained models perform on other historical Japanese documents.
